every other state in the union provides 
specifically for how schools are administered.

27:11.843 --> 27:16.128
that a local school board, elected by the public, 
has full responsibility. And the state has no

27:17.289 --> 27:21.835
responsibility, and the federal government has 
no responsibility. His father saw an opportunity

27:21.855 --> 27:36.392
to grab hold of something that was highly, highly 
emotional at the time, and used it to its fullest

27:21.855 --> 27:36.392
extent, perpetuated himself an officer for the 
next eight years.

27:39.095 --> 27:40.697
That was his only purpose. Only purpose. I can't 
believe that. Did people support Faubus's

27:44.928 --> 27:50.578
actions, the state in general, the community? 
Those who didn't support him kept quiet because it

27:50.638 --> 27:57.831
was highly controversial, highly 
controversial. If you publicly pick a position,

27:59.127 --> 28:14.293
which a lot of us did, who because of the position in 
public life had to, then we became controversial.

28:15.215 --> 28:17.659
And you were either... considered to be a pretty 
good fella or you were a pretty bad fella. And it was

28:22.893 --> 28:24.477
decided a lot by that. Absolutely. Was it totally 
by that? Absolutely. I had friends and even family

28:29.309 --> 28:34.382
members that wouldn't speak to me for two or three 
years because of that. They wouldn't speak to you

28:35.392 --> 28:40.681
because they felt differently or because they 
were afraid to speak out in favor of you? Both.

28:41.202 --> 28:41.803
Both? Both. How was your family treated during 
this time? I read an article about a cross being

28:44.227 --> 28:49.777
burned in your front yard, and I know that your son 
went to high school there. Persecuted.

28:50.919 --> 28:51.139
Persecuted. Was it rough? Real rough? Tense? Not 
really. Not really? Not really when you consider

28:55.528 --> 28:57.732
the reason for it. People did things they wouldn't 
have done otherwise. But people in your own

29:01.379 --> 29:11.239
church, in your own circle of friends,

29:01.379 --> 29:11.239
didn't associate with you. They were... I think 
they were really afraid that they would be drawn

29:12.601 --> 29:19.331
into something that was not their business.

29:23.177 --> 29:26.482
I was concerned about it, but not to any great 
degree. Did they not speak to you even to the extent

29:26.502 --> 29:29.727
of saying hi on the streets? No, not even? No, no. 
Some family members. It took a long time to get over

29:33.192 --> 29:34.915
it. I can imagine. Brent's dad was a senior in high 
school. What kind of treatment did he receive?

29:41.710 --> 29:42.651
Well, he didn't know it. We didn't tell him, but

29:43.933 --> 29:49.880
he was guarded everywhere he went. Undercover? 
Oh, yeah. He was guarded everywhere he went from

29:52.523 --> 30:01.333
the time he left the house until the time he got back 
until school was up the following year. Then he

30:01.813 --> 30:05.398
went to the University of Arkansas the following 
fall. Did he receive any flak there from the

30:06.259 --> 30:10.924
students, or he was just another student then? So

30:12.946 --> 30:18.532
how long after your term did you stay in Little 
Rock? Or did you leave because of this? No, no, no,

30:21.195 --> 30:24.419
no. I had decided that, well,

30:24.439 --> 30:34.570
it became controversial, obviously. I decided to 
run for governor and prepared to file.

30:42.545 --> 30:54.544
I realized that because of the position I had taken 
in this matter right or wrong, that the chance of

30:42.545 --> 30:54.544
being elected was practically nil. And so I 
decided against filing for nomination or

30:56.247 --> 31:04.840
election.

31:06.203 --> 31:13.592
I had been thinking some time about moving our real 
estate business to a larger community. And I think

31:13.612 --> 31:29.612
probably

31:13.612 --> 31:29.612
what happened

31:13.612 --> 31:29.612
probably expedited it to some extent because we 
did business statewide.

31:30.959 --> 31:35.467
I couldn't discuss business if we were talking 
about politics. How large was Little Rock at this

31:35.487 --> 31:36.909
time? Little Rock was about, at that time, was 
about 125,000, 135,000 people. But I felt at that

31:42.760 --> 31:53.659
particular time that I had a, because I was in the 
office at the time, I had a moral responsibility. I

31:54.871 --> 32:05.024
had a Christian responsibility and a legal 
responsibility, constitutional

31:54.871 --> 32:05.024
responsibility. And I did what I did because I felt 
that it was right that they were human beings, not

32:05.044 --> 32:14.676
animals, regardless of color.

32:17.719 --> 32:20.743
I felt that the Christian... The true Christian 
would have done what I did, regardless of

32:22.512 --> 32:27.418
consequences. And the Constitutional State of 
Arkansas, and all other states, says that, by law,

32:28.920 --> 32:44.579
that the chief executive of any city, any city, has 
two primary responsibilities. That is to protect

32:45.140 --> 32:48.464
the lives of people and protect property. I had no 
choice. I had no choice. And I knew when I did it that

32:52.786 --> 32:56.913
I had to pay a price, and my family had to pay a price. 
But I did the same thing a little bit. And I didn't

33:00.419 --> 33:01.741
necessarily agree. In fact, I think the greatest, 
one of the greatest tragedies in the United States

33:01.982 --> 33:18.009
in the history of this country was when the Supreme 
Court made the decision to do away with separate

33:01.982 --> 33:18.009
pedigree besides education. I'll always be. You 
believe it should have remained separate but

33:18.908 --> 33:21.491
equal? To this day, I believe. Because of the 
controversy? No, because I think it's the right

33:23.934 --> 33:26.817
thing to do. You can't force people. You can't 
force people to do something they don't want to do.

33:31.042 --> 33:33.565
You can't force people to associate if they don't 
want to. You can't do it. And we forced, when they

33:35.387 --> 33:45.338
made that decision, and they were forcing people, 
black and white, all colors, They were forcing

33:45.908 --> 33:52.836
people to associate, and you can't do it. I think 
you have a choice. I think you should have a choice

33:54.618 --> 33:59.084
to choose who you want to be your friend and who you 
want to be with. You can't legislate by law who your

33:59.104 --> 34:02.608
friends are going to be. And that's exactly what 
it's all about. And to this day, to this day,

34:05.051 --> 34:08.515
they're doing it. Busing, for example, is the 
greatest, most expensive...

34:16.553 --> 34:18.178
thing this country has to do. When you see kids that 
live in a block or two of a school and have to get on a

34:18.899 --> 34:26.589
bus and ride 25 or 30 miles to go to some school, they 
don't want to, you know. Again, you're taking the

34:26.609 --> 34:35.761
children of this country and you're forcing them 
to do something that they don't want to do. That's

34:35.821 --> 34:36.582
not right. It wasn't right then, it's not right 
today. When we get enough men and women with enough

34:39.085 --> 34:48.417
backbone to go to Washington, D.C. and change it, 
you know, then this country will... and take a step

34:48.397 --> 34:50.799
forward and straighten itself out. And we're in a 
heck of a mess today on so-called civil rights. You

34:54.883 --> 34:58.366
mean change busing or change the whole separate 
but equal? That's just one thing. That's just one

34:59.367 --> 35:01.629
thing. I think we've already pressed the point now 
that they're not going to, that we'll always have,

35:01.649 --> 35:15.021
we'll always have, in my opinion now, some type of 
integrated education. By choice or by? Well. It's

35:17.118 --> 35:18.460
been 30 years. I don't think we can go backwards. 
But if we could, if we could legally, and I thought

35:23.206 --> 35:36.183
that there was enough vote in the Senate and House 
two years ago that it was going to happen. But if we

35:36.283 --> 35:45.235
could do it with a bunch of children in distant 
schools and require, make it where... They go to

35:45.772 --> 35:54.571
schools in their community, you know, that we 
would go a long ways toward getting over the

35:45.772 --> 35:54.571
bitterness that we have. And it's there today. 
It's there and it's going to remain there. Do you

35:58.715 --> 36:16.256
feel like the bitterness has recited some that the 
kids my age, like 20 and younger, are less, I mean

35:58.715 --> 36:16.256
much less, a significant amount less bitter than 
the kids that were in high school when you were

35:58.715 --> 36:16.256
mayor? I don't think so. You don't think so? You 
don't think that there's that much difference

36:18.219 --> 36:20.521
between now and then? I know people today that... 
Their children happen to get on buses and ride 10,

36:23.825 --> 36:28.432
15, 20 miles away to school. And not only do the kids 
resent it, but the parents resent it very much. And

36:36.444 --> 36:46.238
if they're in a position financially, many, many, 
many of them are sending their kids to private

36:36.444 --> 36:46.238
schools for that reason. So when people talk about 
desegregation, integration, in the past tense of

36:48.040 --> 36:54.548
something that's been accomplished, you would 
disagree with that? Oh, yes. Most definitely. Has

36:55.990 --> 36:57.892
not been accomplished. And in my opinion, never 
will be accomplished,

36:57.912 --> 37:02.178
100%. So, okay. Because you're forcing people to 
do something they don't want to do. I agree with

37:06.183 --> 37:07.445
you. Do you have anything else that we left out? 
Anything about your views? Well, my views

37:11.910 --> 37:15.735
really...

37:18.685 --> 37:21.830
haven't changed in 30 odd years. I've never said 
anything publicly, as I told you before.

37:28.160 --> 37:33.389
I went for every year for 15 or 20 years. When 
September rolled around, people all over the

37:33.509 --> 37:41.402
country, media of various types, would try to run 
me down. and seek an interview and get public

37:41.382 --> 37:45.371
statements, and I refused to do it. And still 
would. And still would. I know when I think the 25th

37:49.339 --> 38:00.403
anniversary occurred here two or three years ago.

38:03.775 --> 38:15.488
I had, out of New York and California, major 
television personnel trying to come to Houston

38:03.775 --> 38:15.488
and interview me. And see how your views have 
changed, if at all? I haven't said anything

38:19.313 --> 38:28.643
publicly, and

38:19.313 --> 38:28.643
I've moved to a different district. After you left 
Arkansas, did you move to Houston? Yes. And set up

38:32.304 --> 38:34.086
your business there. And then did you live out here 
at Madisonville for a while? I mean, y'all had a

38:39.894 --> 38:41.476
house over that. We have a ranch up here, a horse 
ranch, and we released the place in January of 82.

38:52.030 --> 38:56.496
And the intent was to build a house here and to live 
here and still have my business operation in

38:57.320 --> 39:03.051
Houston. I had an accident and it became 
impossible. But I will eventually do so. Move back

39:09.683 --> 39:10.604
to Madisonville? Do you have anything else? Did I 
forget anything? Do you have anything to say about

39:15.093 --> 39:19.401
the people or the organizations? Anything that 
we... Maybe we didn't elaborate on enough. The

39:23.321 --> 39:30.511
organizations, even the white citizens' 
councils, did they, and the Ku Klux Klan? Well, of

39:30.531 --> 39:35.838
course, the Ku Klux Klan has been, they've been all 
based on day one, you know. They were such a radical

39:36.139 --> 39:46.834
group that

39:36.139 --> 39:46.834
they should have never existed. The NAACP, not 
quite as bad, but to some extent so biased that

39:48.215 --> 40:08.113
their real purpose for formation and even Martin 
Luther King, the same kind of a situation, you

39:48.215 --> 40:08.113
know, the same kind of a situation. I think the very 
fact that he's eulogized as such a national hero

40:08.093 --> 40:31.671
today is because

40:08.093 --> 40:31.671
he got involved in the stuff that he did and became 
an ineffector, inciting people to do things that

40:08.093 --> 40:31.671
at that particular time were not acceptable, 
trying to rush things too fast.

40:35.178 --> 40:37.301
Do you feel like the black people had had enough? I 
mean, had it up to where they couldn't stand

40:37.682 --> 40:41.267
anymore, and that's why they tried to rush things 
through? They just wanted everything at once? Or

40:43.870 --> 40:44.992
do you just feel like they... I know there's only a 
handful of people, percentage-wise, in any given

40:45.633 --> 40:54.385
cause that will...

40:56.693 --> 41:13.551
become involved to the extent that they give their 
organization or their particular race a bad name,

40:56.693 --> 41:13.551
whether it's civil rights, whether it's 
organized labor, or this, this, or that, or so

40:56.693 --> 41:13.551
forth and so on. There's only a handful of people 
that are troublemakers. By and large, a great

41:17.575 --> 41:24.743
majority of people are reasonable and sensible, 
and they won't get out in front I think that applies

41:27.018 --> 41:32.432
to the Key question plan, the NAACP, and so forth. 
Okay. You can't think of anything else, can you?

41:36.162 --> 41:36.222
No. Thank you. You're welcome.

